OL,4,CEx-BBC boss Tony Hall 'sorry for hurt'
OL,5,Cto royals over Martin Bashir scandal
OL,6, Former BBC director general Tony Hall
OL,7, has said he is "sorry for the hurt
OL,8, caused" to the Royal Family by the
OL,9, scandal surrounding Martin Bashir's
OL,10, 1995 interview with Princess Diana.
OL,12,FAt the time, Lord Hall investigated
OL,13,FBashir's faking of bank documents after
OL,14,Fquestions arose about whether Bashir
OL,15,Fhad used them to secure the scoop.
OL,17,F"I trusted a journalist. I gave him a
OL,18,Fsecond chance. We, the team, gave him a
OL,19,Fsecond chance, and that trust was
OL,20,Fabused and was misplaced," Lord Hall
OL,21,Ftold a committee of MPs on Tuesday.
